### Code

```lean
have h₁ : (b, ! S b) ∉ S⌈σ⌉a := by
  intro h
  have h₂ := @indistinguishable_then_same_values n a (S, ⟨σ, _⟩) (T, ⟨τ, _⟩) equ'
  simp only [Prod.mk.injEq] at h₂
  have h₃ := h₂
  simp only [h] at h₃
  simp only [Not.not] at h₃
  have h₄ : (b, ! S b) ∈ S⌈σ⌉a := by assumption
  have h₅ : (b, ! S b) ∈ T⌈τ⌉a := by
    simp_all [h₂, Set.mem_setOf_eq]
  simp_all [h₂, Set.mem_setOf_eq]
  <;> aesop
```

### Explanation

1. **Assumption for Contradiction**: We assume `(b, ! S b) ∈ S⌈σ⌉a`.
2. **Indistinguishability Implies Same Value**: By `indistinguishable_then_same_values`, `S⌈σ⌉a = T⌈τ⌉a`.
